description:
This group is aimed at Film lovers, within all aspects of Films. No Film, story or subject is off limits. The wider range of choice the better. Any events that associate with the world of Film will be also welcomed.

There are a few Film festivals within Stockholm depending on the time of year. So we have a wide range of choice of Films from the Festival's also outdoor locations

Depending on what the group's inclination is, this group could be a gang that goes to see movies together or it could be a group that organizes film nights. It is open to all who are interested in and/or work in film.

category.name: movies/film
description:
Do you have a passion for film making or an interest in making movies? Whether you are a professional looking for collaborators, or a lover of films, you are welcome to join our group. The main aim of this group is to encourage creatives to implement their ideas in filmmaking and to bring ideas to life. 

There are many skilled and imaginative people out there, all they need is support and a network. One of the goals of this group is to work collectively most weekends and to complete one film a month. 

From time to time, we will organize workshops, seminars, outings, screenings, and the like, to further expand on our creative atmosphere and common love for film and filmmaking.

The concept of this group is simple, on weekends members of this group will meet and brainstorm ideas for producing a short format movie (under 15 minutes), then agree on a concept to produce for that month. We will bring projects from idea to script, through pre-production, production, and into final product by the end of the month. In other words, we will collaborate on shaping ideas, provide support during scriptwriting, shooting the short film, edit the footage, then publish the project online.

Please Note: This group is only for people who are passionate, respectful, and understanding. 
Just to confirm, this group will not generate any revenue in any case. We want to create and share our creations.
Everyone should contribute in some way or the other.
Since this is a non-profit group, time, equipment and resources needed for shooting films will be shared within the group members. We are here to help each other to create fun and exciting projects. Does this sound interesting? Step up, let's breathe new life into the ideas in our heads. If you have any questions please feel free to ask. Looking forward to see you. :)
name: Stockholm Filmmakers Collective
organizer.name: Ranjith Engu

category.name: movies/film
description:
Stockholm International Film Club is an ambitious Swedish Meetup initiative that endeavors to fuse quality contemporary cinema with commercial cinematic products from across the globe. The goal is to showcase, without any bias of origin or language, quality feature-films to the expats as well as the native audience residing in Sweden. This Meetup Group will exclusively acquire the rights to high quality international feature films for Sweden, and accordingly plan and schedule meetup events for anyone and everyone interested in quality cinema to come together, connect, network and share that common interest i.e. films!

Who should join?

Any film enthusiast, movie buff, film-goer; who is sincerely interested in experiencing the best of world cinema must join. With us, its not the Hollywood or Bollywood that matters, its not Europe or Asia that matters; what will make this film club meetup unique is the focus on content - the theme, the message, the cinematic experience - where cinema is an art which is honest, enjoyable, entertaining and at times, even hard-hitting.

What members can expect of the group, and what we expect of them.

We will introduce our members to the kind of cinema which has a message - on international issues, on social issues, on geopolitical issues - that can bring communities together, make them discuss on issues of relevance - presented in a format which is both enjoyable and entertaining. We wish that our members will come together to experience cinema as medium that will bring them together to watch, think, introspect and discuss on issues of relevance. 

Come together and have a good laugh!.........its as simple as that :-)
name: Stockholm International Film Club
organizer.name: Nishant Jain

Kaleidoscope is a community for Virtual Reality Creators. Bringing together artists & engineers from cinema, gaming, and tech, Kaleidoscope explores virtual reality as a storytelling medium and celebrates the pioneers of this new art form. Creatives from all backgrounds are welcome!

We will host quarterly "Salons" where the community can showcase their virtual reality films, art, games, and immersive experiences. As a group, we will share knowledge, get feedback on projects, and show off our latest creations. 

We can't wait to meet you all! If you are interested in becoming a local organizer please email nick@kaleidovr.com. For more information about us, please visit kaleidovr.com.

Copenhagen Cinema Club is for those who would like to enjoy films (and maybe coffe, drinks or food afterwards) with other people. You will normally find a wide range of independent, foreign and Danish films on this Meetup group, while Hollywood blockbusters will also pop up occasionally. 

The usual format is that we meet 30 min before the film and have a chat with each other in the cinema. After a movie, those, who have time, can join the group to a nearby cafe for a chat. 

Do you want to watch a specific movie? You are very welcome to post your suggestion on the meetup page or send a message to organizers. If you want, you can also become an organizer and post an event any time you want.

description:
Hi and thanks a lot for joining Copenhagen Blowjob Academy!

Please take a hard look at the calendar for an overview of meetups. Or use the 'Upcoming'/'Suggested' sections.

Our Concept:

We typically meet at an inexpensive to midrange restaurant for dinner, then head to the movies, sometimes followed by a post-movie group debriefing. During weekends, we sometimes meet for brunch and watch a movie afterwards.

What kind of movies do we like? Traditionally, we have watched a wide variety of movies, ranging from sci-fi and 3D movies to artsy movies. Hopefully you will find something you will like, or you can suggest a movie and be appointed event organizer. <br>

We expect participants at our social events to be well-mannered and -groomed. When someone does not know the Danish language, we will speak English. Check out the language of the next movie in the calendar. Most often, we will choose films with English-speaking characters, but occasionally, we may watch a movie that requires that you can read Danish subtitles.

Always bring cash to pay for the movie ticket at the event – or alternatively, bring a smart phone with the app Mobile Pay.

category.name: movies/film
description:
Copenhagen Cinema Club is for those who would like to enjoy films (and maybe coffe, drinks or food afterwards) with other people. You will normally find a wide range of independent, foreign and Danish films on this Meetup group, while Hollywood blockbusters will also pop up occasionally. 

The usual format is that we meet 30 min before the film and have a chat with each other in the cinema. After a movie, those, who have time, can join the group to a nearby cafe for a chat. 

Do you want to watch a specific movie? You are very welcome to post your suggestion on the meetup page or send a message to organizers. If you want, you can also become an organizer and post an event any time you want.

category.name: movies/film
description:
Do you have a passion for film making or an interest in making movies? Whether you are a professional looking for collaborators, or a lover of films, you are welcome to join our group. The main aim of this group is to encourage creatives to implement their ideas in filmmaking and to bring ideas to life. 

There are many skilled and imaginative people out there, all they need is support and a network. One of the goals of this group is to work collectively most weekends and to complete one film a month. 

From time to time, we will organize workshops, seminars, outings, screenings, and the like, to further expand on our creative atmosphere and common love for film and filmmaking.

The concept of this group is simple, on weekends members of this group will meet and brainstorm ideas for producing a short format movie (under 15 minutes), then agree on a concept to produce for that month. We will bring projects from idea to script, through pre-production, production, and into final product by the end of the month. In other words, we will collaborate on shaping ideas, provide support during scriptwriting, shooting the short film, edit the footage, then publish the project online.

Please Note: This group is only for people who are passionate, respectful, and understanding. 
Just to confirm, this group will not generate any revenue in any case. We want to create and share our creations.
Everyone should contribute in some way or the other.
Since this is a non-profit group, time, equipment and resources needed for shooting films will be shared within the group members. We are here to help each other to create fun and exciting projects. Does this sound interesting? Step up, let's breathe new life into the ideas in our heads. If you have any questions please feel free to ask. Looking forward to see you. :)
name: Stockholm Filmmakers Collective
organizer.name: Ranjith Engu

category.name: movies/film
description:
Stockholm International Film Club is an ambitious Swedish Meetup initiative that endeavors to fuse quality contemporary cinema with commercial cinematic products from across the globe. The goal is to showcase, without any bias of origin or language, quality feature-films to the expats as well as the native audience residing in Sweden. This Meetup Group will exclusively acquire the rights to high quality international feature films for Sweden, and accordingly plan and schedule meetup events for anyone and everyone interested in quality cinema to come together, connect, network and share that common interest i.e. films!

Who should join?

Any film enthusiast, movie buff, film-goer; who is sincerely interested in experiencing the best of world cinema must join. With us, its not the Hollywood or Bollywood that matters, its not Europe or Asia that matters; what will make this film club meetup unique is the focus on content - the theme, the message, the cinematic experience - where cinema is an art which is honest, enjoyable, entertaining and at times, even hard-hitting.

What members can expect of the group, and what we expect of them.

We will introduce our members to the kind of cinema which has a message - on international issues, on social issues, on geopolitical issues - that can bring communities together, make them discuss on issues of relevance - presented in a format which is both enjoyable and entertaining. We wish that our members will come together to experience cinema as medium that will bring them together to watch, think, introspect and discuss on issues of relevance. 

Come together and have a good laugh!.........its as simple as that :-)
name: Stockholm International Film Club

description:
Kaleidoscope is a community for Virtual Reality Creators. Bringing together artists & engineers from cinema, gaming, and tech, Kaleidoscope explores virtual reality as a storytelling medium and celebrates the pioneers of this new art form. Creatives from all backgrounds are welcome!

We will host quarterly "Salons" where the community can showcase their virtual reality films, art, games, and immersive experiences. As a group, we will share knowledge, get feedback on projects, and show off our latest creations. 

We can't wait to meet you all! If you are interested in becoming a local organizer please email nick@kaleidovr.com. For more information about us, please visit kaleidovr.com.
name: Kaleidoscope STO // Virtual Reality Film, Art, & Experiences

category.name: movies/film
description:
Do you have a passion for film making or an interest in making movies? Whether you are a professional looking for collaborators, or a lover of films, you are welcome to join our group. The main aim of this group is to encourage creatives to implement their ideas in filmmaking and to bring ideas to life. 

There are many skilled and imaginative people out there, all they need is support and a network. One of the goals of this group is to work collectively most weekends and to complete one film a month. 

From time to time, we will organize workshops, seminars, outings, screenings, and the like, to further expand on our creative atmosphere and common love for film and filmmaking.

The concept of this group is simple, on weekends members of this group will meet and brainstorm ideas for producing a short format movie (under 15 minutes), then agree on a concept to produce for that month. We will bring projects from idea to script, through pre-production, production, and into final product by the end of the month. In other words, we will collaborate on shaping ideas, provide support during scriptwriting, shooting the short film, edit the footage, then publish the project online.

Please Note: This group is only for people who are passionate, respectful, and understanding. 
Just to confirm, this group will not generate any revenue in any case. We want to create and share our creations.
Everyone should contribute in some way or the other.
Since this is a non-profit group, time, equipment and resources needed for shooting films will be shared within the group members. We are here to help each other to create fun and exciting projects. Does this sound interesting? Step up, let's breathe new life into the ideas in our heads. If you have any questions please feel free to ask. Looking forward to see you. :)
name: Stockholm Filmmakers Collective
organizer.name: Ranjith Engu

category.name: movies/film
description:
Stockholm International Film Club is an ambitious Swedish Meetup initiative that endeavors to fuse quality contemporary cinema with commercial cinematic products from across the globe. The goal is to showcase, without any bias of origin or language, quality feature-films to the expats as well as the native audience residing in Sweden. This Meetup Group will exclusively acquire the rights to high quality international feature films for Sweden, and accordingly plan and schedule meetup events for anyone and everyone interested in quality cinema to come together, connect, network and share that common interest i.e. films!

Who should join?

Any film enthusiast, movie buff, film-goer; who is sincerely interested in experiencing the best of world cinema must join. With us, its not the Hollywood or Bollywood that matters, its not Europe or Asia that matters; what will make this film club meetup unique is the focus on content - the theme, the message, the cinematic experience - where cinema is an art which is honest, enjoyable, entertaining and at times, even hard-hitting.

What members can expect of the group, and what we expect of them.

We will introduce our members to the kind of cinema which has a message - on international issues, on social issues, on geopolitical issues - that can bring communities together, make them discuss on issues of relevance - presented in a format which is both enjoyable and entertaining. We wish that our members will come together to experience cinema as medium that will bring them together to watch, think, introspect and discuss on issues of relevance. 

Come together and have a good laugh!.........its as simple as that :-)
name: Stockholm International Film Club
organizer.name: Nishant Jain

category.name: movies/film
description:
Kaleidoscope is a community for Virtual Reality Creators. Bringing together artists & engineers from cinema, gaming, and tech, Kaleidoscope explores virtual reality as a storytelling medium and celebrates the pioneers of this new art form. Creatives from all backgrounds are welcome!

We will host quarterly "Salons" where the community can showcase their virtual reality films, art, games, and immersive experiences. As a group, we will share knowledge, get feedback on projects, and show off our latest creations. 

We can't wait to meet you all! If you are interested in becoming a local organizer please email nick@kaleidovr.com. For more information about us, please visit kaleidovr.com.
name: Kaleidoscope STO // Virtual Reality Film, Art, & Experiences

category.name: movies/film
description:
Do you have a passion for film making or an interest in making movies? Whether you are a professional looking for collaborators, or a lover of films, you are welcome to join our group. The main aim of this group is to encourage creatives to implement their ideas in filmmaking and to bring ideas to life. 

There are many skilled and imaginative people out there, all they need is support and a network. One of the goals of this group is to work collectively most weekends and to complete one film a month. 

From time to time, we will organize workshops, seminars, outings, screenings, and the like, to further expand on our creative atmosphere and common love for film and filmmaking.

The concept of this group is simple, on weekends members of this group will meet and brainstorm ideas for producing a short format movie (under 15 minutes), then agree on a concept to produce for that month. We will bring projects from idea to script, through pre-production, production, and into final product by the end of the month. In other words, we will collaborate on shaping ideas, provide support during scriptwriting, shooting the short film, edit the footage, then publish the project online.

Please Note: This group is only for people who are passionate, respectful, and understanding. 
Just to confirm, this group will not generate any revenue in any case. We want to create and share our creations.
Everyone should contribute in some way or the other.
Since this is a non-profit group, time, equipment and resources needed for shooting films will be shared within the group members. We are here to help each other to create fun and exciting projects. Does this sound interesting? Step up, let's breathe new life into the ideas in our heads. If you have any questions please feel free to ask. Looking forward to see you. :)
name: Stockholm Filmmakers Collective
organizer.name: Ranjith Engu

category.name: movies/film
description:
Stockholm International Film Club is an ambitious Swedish Meetup initiative that endeavors to fuse quality contemporary cinema with commercial cinematic products from across the globe. The goal is to showcase, without any bias of origin or language, quality feature-films to the expats as well as the native audience residing in Sweden. This Meetup Group will exclusively acquire the rights to high quality international feature films for Sweden, and accordingly plan and schedule meetup events for anyone and everyone interested in quality cinema to come together, connect, network and share that common interest i.e. films!

Who should join?

Any film enthusiast, movie buff, film-goer; who is sincerely interested in experiencing the best of world cinema must join. With us, its not the Hollywood or Bollywood that matters, its not Europe or Asia that matters; what will make this film club meetup unique is the focus on content - the theme, the message, the cinematic experience - where cinema is an art which is honest, enjoyable, entertaining and at times, even hard-hitting.

What members can expect of the group, and what we expect of them.

We will introduce our members to the kind of cinema which has a message - on international issues, on social issues, on geopolitical issues - that can bring communities together, make them discuss on issues of relevance - presented in a format which is both enjoyable and entertaining. We wish that our members will come together to experience cinema as medium that will bring them together to watch, think, introspect and discuss on issues of relevance. 

Come together and have a good laugh!.........its as simple as that :-)
name: Stockholm International Film Club

category.name: movies/film
description:
Copenhagen Cinema Club is for those who would like to enjoy films (and maybe coffe, drinks or food afterwards) with other people. You will normally find a wide range of independent, foreign and Danish films on this Meetup group, while Hollywood blockbusters will also pop up occasionally. 

The usual format is that we meet 30 min before the film and have a chat with each other in the cinema. After a movie, those, who have time, can join the group to a nearby cafe for a chat. 

Do you want to watch a specific movie? You are very welcome to post your suggestion on the meetup page or send a message to organizers. If you want, you can also become an organizer and post an event any time you want.
name: Copenhagen Cinema Club

category.name: movies/film
description:
Hi and thanks a lot for joining Copenhagen Blowjob Academy!

Please take a hard look at the calendar for an overview of meetups. Or use the 'Upcoming'/'Suggested' sections.

Our Concept:

We typically meet at an inexpensive to midrange restaurant for dinner, then head to the movies, sometimes followed by a post-movie group debriefing. During weekends, we sometimes meet for brunch and watch a movie afterwards.

What kind of movies do we like? Traditionally, we have watched a wide variety of movies, ranging from sci-fi and 3D movies to artsy movies. Hopefully you will find something you will like, or you can suggest a movie and be appointed event organizer. <br>

We expect participants at our social events to be well-mannered and -groomed. When someone does not know the Danish language, we will speak English. Check out the language of the next movie in the calendar. Most often, we will choose films with English-speaking characters, but occasionally, we may watch a movie that requires that you can read Danish subtitles.

Always bring cash to pay for the movie ticket at the event – or alternatively, bring a smart phone with the app Mobile Pay.
name: Copenhagen Blowjob Academy

description: The world of films is indeed exciting. For most of us who have a passion, it does seem impossible to be part of a movie production to learn more about the craft. category.name: movies/film
description:
Do you have a passion for film making or an interest in making movies? Whether you are a professional looking for collaborators, or a lover of films, you are welcome to join our group. The main aim of this group is to encourage creatives to implement their ideas in filmmaking and to bring ideas to life. 

There are many skilled and imaginative people out there, all they need is support and a network. One of the goals of this group is to work collectively most weekends and to complete one film a month. 

From time to time, we will organize workshops, seminars, outings, screenings, and the like, to further expand on our creative atmosphere and common love for film and filmmaking.

The concept of this group is simple, on weekends members of this group will meet and brainstorm ideas for producing a short format movie (under 15 minutes), then agree on a concept to produce for that month. We will bring projects from idea to script, through pre-production, production, and into final product by the end of the month. In other words, we will collaborate on shaping ideas, provide support during scriptwriting, shooting the short film, edit the footage, then publish the project online.

Please Note: This group is only for people who are passionate, respectful, and understanding. 
Just to confirm, this group will not generate any revenue in any case. We want to create and share our creations.
Everyone should contribute in some way or the other.
Since this is a non-profit group, time, equipment and resources needed for shooting films will be shared within the group members. We are here to help each other to create fun and exciting projects. Does this sound interesting? Step up, let's breathe new life into the ideas in our heads. If you have any questions please feel free to ask. Looking forward to see you. :)
name: Stockholm Filmmakers Collective
organizer.name: Ranjith Engu

category.name: movies/film
description:
Stockholm International Film Club is an ambitious Swedish Meetup initiative that endeavors to fuse quality contemporary cinema with commercial cinematic products from across the globe. The goal is to showcase, without any bias of origin or language, quality feature-films to the expats as well as the native audience residing in Sweden. This Meetup Group will exclusively acquire the rights to high quality international feature films for Sweden, and accordingly plan and schedule meetup events for anyone and everyone interested in quality cinema to come together, connect, network and share that common interest i.e. films!

Who should join?

Any film enthusiast, movie buff, film-goer; who is sincerely interested in experiencing the best of world cinema must join. With us, its not the Hollywood or Bollywood that matters, its not Europe or Asia that matters; what will make this film club meetup unique is the focus on content - the theme, the message, the cinematic experience - where cinema is an art which is honest, enjoyable, entertaining and at times, even hard-hitting.

What members can expect of the group, and what we expect of them.

We will introduce our members to the kind of cinema which has a message - on international issues, on social issues, on geopolitical issues - that can bring communities together, make them discuss on issues of relevance - presented in a format which is both enjoyable and entertaining. We wish that our members will come together to experience cinema as medium that will bring them together to watch, think, introspect and discuss on issues of relevance. 

Come together and have a good laugh!.........its as simple as that :-)
name: Stockholm International Film Club
organizer.name: Nishant Jain

description:
Kaleidoscope is a community for Virtual Reality Creators. Bringing together artists & engineers from cinema, gaming, and tech, Kaleidoscope explores virtual reality as a storytelling medium and celebrates the pioneers of this new art form. Creatives from all backgrounds are welcome!

We will host quarterly "Salons" where the community can showcase their virtual reality films, art, games, and immersive experiences. As a group, we will share knowledge, get feedback on projects, and show off our latest creations. 

We can't wait to meet you all! If you are interested in becoming a local organizer please email nick@kaleidovr.com. For more information about us, please visit kaleidovr.com.

description:
Copenhagen Cinema Club is for those who would like to enjoy films (and maybe coffe, drinks or food afterwards) with other people. You will normally find a wide range of independent, foreign and Danish films on this Meetup group, while Hollywood blockbusters will also pop up occasionally. 

The usual format is that we meet 30 min before the film and have a chat with each other in the cinema. After a movie, those, who have time, can join the group to a nearby cafe for a chat. 

Do you want to watch a specific movie? You are very welcome to post your suggestion on the meetup page or send a message to organizers. If you want, you can also become an organizer and post an event any time you want.

category.name: movies/film
description:
Hi and thanks a lot for joining Copenhagen Blowjob Academy!

Please take a hard look at the calendar for an overview of meetups. Or use the 'Upcoming'/'Suggested' sections.

Our Concept:

We typically meet at an inexpensive to midrange restaurant for dinner, then head to the movies, sometimes followed by a post-movie group debriefing. During weekends, we sometimes meet for brunch and watch a movie afterwards.

What kind of movies do we like? Traditionally, we have watched a wide variety of movies, ranging from sci-fi and 3D movies to artsy movies. Hopefully you will find something you will like, or you can suggest a movie and be appointed event organizer. <br>

We expect participants at our social events to be well-mannered and -groomed. When someone does not know the Danish language, we will speak English. Check out the language of the next movie in the calendar. Most often, we will choose films with English-speaking characters, but occasionally, we may watch a movie that requires that you can read Danish subtitles.

Always bring cash to pay for the movie ticket at the event – or alternatively, bring a smart phone with the app Mobile Pay.

category.name: movies/film
description:
Do you have a passion for film making or an interest in making movies? Whether you are a professional looking for collaborators, or a lover of films, you are welcome to join our group. The main aim of this group is to encourage creatives to implement their ideas in filmmaking and to bring ideas to life. 

There are many skilled and imaginative people out there, all they need is support and a network. One of the goals of this group is to work collectively most weekends and to complete one film a month. 

From time to time, we will organize workshops, seminars, outings, screenings, and the like, to further expand on our creative atmosphere and common love for film and filmmaking.

The concept of this group is simple, on weekends members of this group will meet and brainstorm ideas for producing a short format movie (under 15 minutes), then agree on a concept to produce for that month. We will bring projects from idea to script, through pre-production, production, and into final product by the end of the month. In other words, we will collaborate on shaping ideas, provide support during scriptwriting, shooting the short film, edit the footage, then publish the project online.

Please Note: This group is only for people who are passionate, respectful, and understanding. 
Just to confirm, this group will not generate any revenue in any case. We want to create and share our creations.
Everyone should contribute in some way or the other.
Since this is a non-profit group, time, equipment and resources needed for shooting films will be shared within the group members. We are here to help each other to create fun and exciting projects. Does this sound interesting? Step up, let's breathe new life into the ideas in our heads. If you have any questions please feel free to ask. Looking forward to see you. :)
name: Stockholm Filmmakers Collective

category.name: movies/film
description:
Stockholm International Film Club is an ambitious Swedish Meetup initiative that endeavors to fuse quality contemporary cinema with commercial cinematic products from across the globe. The goal is to showcase, without any bias of origin or language, quality feature-films to the expats as well as the native audience residing in Sweden. This Meetup Group will exclusively acquire the rights to high quality international feature films for Sweden, and accordingly plan and schedule meetup events for anyone and everyone interested in quality cinema to come together, connect, network and share that common interest i.e. films!

Who should join?

Any film enthusiast, movie buff, film-goer; who is sincerely interested in experiencing the best of world cinema must join. With us, its not the Hollywood or Bollywood that matters, its not Europe or Asia that matters; what will make this film club meetup unique is the focus on content - the theme, the message, the cinematic experience - where cinema is an art which is honest, enjoyable, entertaining and at times, even hard-hitting.

What members can expect of the group, and what we expect of them.

We will introduce our members to the kind of cinema which has a message - on international issues, on social issues, on geopolitical issues - that can bring communities together, make them discuss on issues of relevance - presented in a format which is both enjoyable and entertaining. We wish that our members will come together to experience cinema as medium that will bring them together to watch, think, introspect and discuss on issues of relevance. 

Come together and have a good laugh!.........its as simple as that :-)
name: Stockholm International Film Club

Kaleidoscope is a community for Virtual Reality Creators. Bringing together artists & engineers from cinema, gaming, and tech, Kaleidoscope explores virtual reality as a storytelling medium and celebrates the pioneers of this new art form. Creatives from all backgrounds are welcome!

We will host quarterly "Salons" where the community can showcase their virtual reality films, art, games, and immersive experiences. As a group, we will share knowledge, get feedback on projects, and show off our latest creations. 

We can't wait to meet you all! If you are interested in becoming a local organizer please email nick@kaleidovr.com. For more information about us, please visit kaleidovr.com.

category.name: movies/film
description:
Do you have a passion for film making or an interest in making movies? Whether you are a professional looking for collaborators, or a lover of films, you are welcome to join our group. The main aim of this group is to encourage creatives to implement their ideas in filmmaking and to bring ideas to life. 

There are many skilled and imaginative people out there, all they need is support and a network. One of the goals of this group is to work collectively most weekends and to complete one film a month. 

From time to time, we will organize workshops, seminars, outings, screenings, and the like, to further expand on our creative atmosphere and common love for film and filmmaking.

The concept of this group is simple, on weekends members of this group will meet and brainstorm ideas for producing a short format movie (under 15 minutes), then agree on a concept to produce for that month. We will bring projects from idea to script, through pre-production, production, and into final product by the end of the month. In other words, we will collaborate on shaping ideas, provide support during scriptwriting, shooting the short film, edit the footage, then publish the project online.

Please Note: This group is only for people who are passionate, respectful, and understanding. 
Just to confirm, this group will not generate any revenue in any case. We want to create and share our creations.
Everyone should contribute in some way or the other.
Since this is a non-profit group, time, equipment and resources needed for shooting films will be shared within the group members. We are here to help each other to create fun and exciting projects. Does this sound interesting? Step up, let's breathe new life into the ideas in our heads. If you have any questions please feel free to ask. Looking forward to see you. :)
name: Stockholm Filmmakers Collective
organizer.name: Ranjith Engu

category.name: movies/film
description:
Stockholm International Film Club is an ambitious Swedish Meetup initiative that endeavors to fuse quality contemporary cinema with commercial cinematic products from across the globe. The goal is to showcase, without any bias of origin or language, quality feature-films to the expats as well as the native audience residing in Sweden. This Meetup Group will exclusively acquire the rights to high quality international feature films for Sweden, and accordingly plan and schedule meetup events for anyone and everyone interested in quality cinema to come together, connect, network and share that common interest i.e. films!

Who should join?

Any film enthusiast, movie buff, film-goer; who is sincerely interested in experiencing the best of world cinema must join. With us, its not the Hollywood or Bollywood that matters, its not Europe or Asia that matters; what will make this film club meetup unique is the focus on content - the theme, the message, the cinematic experience - where cinema is an art which is honest, enjoyable, entertaining and at times, even hard-hitting.

What members can expect of the group, and what we expect of them.

We will introduce our members to the kind of cinema which has a message - on international issues, on social issues, on geopolitical issues - that can bring communities together, make them discuss on issues of relevance - presented in a format which is both enjoyable and entertaining. We wish that our members will come together to experience cinema as medium that will bring them together to watch, think, introspect and discuss on issues of relevance. 

Come together and have a good laugh!.........its as simple as that :-)
name: Stockholm International Film Club

description:
Kaleidoscope is a community for Virtual Reality Creators. Bringing together artists & engineers from cinema, gaming, and tech, Kaleidoscope explores virtual reality as a storytelling medium and celebrates the pioneers of this new art form. Creatives from all backgrounds are welcome!

We will host quarterly "Salons" where the community can showcase their virtual reality films, art, games, and immersive experiences. As a group, we will share knowledge, get feedback on projects, and show off our latest creations. 

We can't wait to meet you all! If you are interested in becoming a local organizer please email nick@kaleidovr.com. For more information about us, please visit kaleidovr.com.
name: Kaleidoscope STO // Virtual Reality Film, Art, & Experiences

There are many skilled and imaginative people out there, all they need is support and a network. One of the goals of this group is to work collectively most weekends and to complete one film a month. 

From time to time, we will organize workshops, seminars, outings, screenings, and the like, to further expand on our creative atmosphere and common love for film and filmmaking.

The concept of this group is simple, on weekends members of this group will meet and brainstorm ideas for producing a short format movie (under 15 minutes), then agree on a concept to produce for that month. We will bring projects from idea to script, through pre-production, production, and into final product by the end of the month. In other words, we will collaborate on shaping ideas, provide support during scriptwriting, shooting the short film, edit the footage, then publish the project online.

Please Note: This group is only for people who are passionate, respectful, and understanding. 
Just to confirm, this group will not generate any revenue in any case. We want to create and share our creations.
Everyone should contribute in some way or the other.
Since this is a non-profit group, time, equipment and resources needed for shooting films will be shared within the group members. We are here to help each other to create fun and exciting projects. Does this sound interesting? Step up, let's breathe new life into the ideas in our heads. If you have any questions please feel free to ask. Looking forward to see you. :)
name: Stockholm Filmmakers Collective

category.name: movies/film
description:
Stockholm International Film Club is an ambitious Swedish Meetup initiative that endeavors to fuse quality contemporary cinema with commercial cinematic products from across the globe. The goal is to showcase, without any bias of origin or language, quality feature-films to the expats as well as the native audience residing in Sweden. This Meetup Group will exclusively acquire the rights to high quality international feature films for Sweden, and accordingly plan and schedule meetup events for anyone and everyone interested in quality cinema to come together, connect, network and share that common interest i.e. films!

Who should join?

Any film enthusiast, movie buff, film-goer; who is sincerely interested in experiencing the best of world cinema must join. With us, its not the Hollywood or Bollywood that matters, its not Europe or Asia that matters; what will make this film club meetup unique is the focus on content - the theme, the message, the cinematic experience - where cinema is an art which is honest, enjoyable, entertaining and at times, even hard-hitting.

What members can expect of the group, and what we expect of them.

We will introduce our members to the kind of cinema which has a message - on international issues, on social issues, on geopolitical issues - that can bring communities together, make them discuss on issues of relevance - presented in a format which is both enjoyable and entertaining. We wish that our members will come together to experience cinema as medium that will bring them together to watch, think, introspect and discuss on issues of relevance. 

Come together and have a good laugh!.........its as simple as that :-)
name: Stockholm International Film Club
organizer.name: Nishant Jain

category.name: movies/film
description:
Do you have a passion for film making or an interest in making movies? Whether you are a professional looking for collaborators, or a lover of films, you are welcome to join our group. The main aim of this group is to encourage creatives to implement their ideas in filmmaking and to bring ideas to life. 

There are many skilled and imaginative people out there, all they need is support and a network. One of the goals of this group is to work collectively most weekends and to complete one film a month. 

From time to time, we will organize workshops, seminars, outings, screenings, and the like, to further expand on our creative atmosphere and common love for film and filmmaking.

The concept of this group is simple, on weekends members of this group will meet and brainstorm ideas for producing a short format movie (under 15 minutes), then agree on a concept to produce for that month. We will bring projects from idea to script, through pre-production, production, and into final product by the end of the month. In other words, we will collaborate on shaping ideas, provide support during scriptwriting, shooting the short film, edit the footage, then publish the project online.

Please Note: This group is only for people who are passionate, respectful, and understanding. 
Just to confirm, this group will not generate any revenue in any case. We want to create and share our creations.
Everyone should contribute in some way or the other.
Since this is a non-profit group, time, equipment and resources needed for shooting films will be shared within the group members. We are here to help each other to create fun and exciting projects. Does this sound interesting? Step up, let's breathe new life into the ideas in our heads. If you have any questions please feel free to ask. Looking forward to see you. :)
name: Stockholm Filmmakers Collective
organizer.name: Ranjith Engu

category.name: movies/film
description:
Stockholm International Film Club is an ambitious Swedish Meetup initiative that endeavors to fuse quality contemporary cinema with commercial cinematic products from across the globe. The goal is to showcase, without any bias of origin or language, quality feature-films to the expats as well as the native audience residing in Sweden. This Meetup Group will exclusively acquire the rights to high quality international feature films for Sweden, and accordingly plan and schedule meetup events for anyone and everyone interested in quality cinema to come together, connect, network and share that common interest i.e. films!

Who should join?

Any film enthusiast, movie buff, film-goer; who is sincerely interested in experiencing the best of world cinema must join. With us, its not the Hollywood or Bollywood that matters, its not Europe or Asia that matters; what will make this film club meetup unique is the focus on content - the theme, the message, the cinematic experience - where cinema is an art which is honest, enjoyable, entertaining and at times, even hard-hitting.

What members can expect of the group, and what we expect of them.

We will introduce our members to the kind of cinema which has a message - on international issues, on social issues, on geopolitical issues - that can bring communities together, make them discuss on issues of relevance - presented in a format which is both enjoyable and entertaining. We wish that our members will come together to experience cinema as medium that will bring them together to watch, think, introspect and discuss on issues of relevance. 

Come together and have a good laugh!.........its as simple as that :-)
name: Stockholm International Film Club
organizer.name: Nishant Jain

category.name: movies/film
description:
Kaleidoscope is a community for Virtual Reality Creators. Bringing together artists & engineers from cinema, gaming, and tech, Kaleidoscope explores virtual reality as a storytelling medium and celebrates the pioneers of this new art form. Creatives from all backgrounds are welcome!

We will host quarterly "Salons" where the community can showcase their virtual reality films, art, games, and immersive experiences. As a group, we will share knowledge, get feedback on projects, and show off our latest creations. 

We can't wait to meet you all! If you are interested in becoming a local organizer please email nick@kaleidovr.com. For more information about us, please visit kaleidovr.com.
name: Kaleidoscope STO // Virtual Reality Film, Art, & Experiences

category.name: movies/film
description:
Do you have a passion for film making or an interest in making movies? Whether you are a professional looking for collaborators, or a lover of films, you are welcome to join our group. The main aim of this group is to encourage creatives to implement their ideas in filmmaking and to bring ideas to life. 

There are many skilled and imaginative people out there, all they need is support and a network. One of the goals of this group is to work collectively most weekends and to complete one film a month. 

From time to time, we will organize workshops, seminars, outings, screenings, and the like, to further expand on our creative atmosphere and common love for film and filmmaking.

The concept of this group is simple, on weekends members of this group will meet and brainstorm ideas for producing a short format movie (under 15 minutes), then agree on a concept to produce for that month. We will bring projects from idea to script, through pre-production, production, and into final product by the end of the month. In other words, we will collaborate on shaping ideas, provide support during scriptwriting, shooting the short film, edit the footage, then publish the project online.

Please Note: This group is only for people who are passionate, respectful, and understanding. 
Just to confirm, this group will not generate any revenue in any case. We want to create and share our creations.
Everyone should contribute in some way or the other.
Since this is a non-profit group, time, equipment and resources needed for shooting films will be shared within the group members. We are here to help each other to create fun and exciting projects. Does this sound interesting? Step up, let's breathe new life into the ideas in our heads. If you have any questions please feel free to ask. Looking forward to see you. :)
name: Stockholm Filmmakers Collective
organizer.name: Ranjith Engu

category.name: movies/film
description:
Stockholm International Film Club is an ambitious Swedish Meetup initiative that endeavors to fuse quality contemporary cinema with commercial cinematic products from across the globe. The goal is to showcase, without any bias of origin or language, quality feature-films to the expats as well as the native audience residing in Sweden. This Meetup Group will exclusively acquire the rights to high quality international feature films for Sweden, and accordingly plan and schedule meetup events for anyone and everyone interested in quality cinema to come together, connect, network and share that common interest i.e. films!

Who should join?

Any film enthusiast, movie buff, film-goer; who is sincerely interested in experiencing the best of world cinema must join. With us, its not the Hollywood or Bollywood that matters, its not Europe or Asia that matters; what will make this film club meetup unique is the focus on content - the theme, the message, the cinematic experience - where cinema is an art which is honest, enjoyable, entertaining and at times, even hard-hitting.

What members can expect of the group, and what we expect of them.

We will introduce our members to the kind of cinema which has a message - on international issues, on social issues, on geopolitical issues - that can bring communities together, make them discuss on issues of relevance - presented in a format which is both enjoyable and entertaining. We wish that our members will come together to experience cinema as medium that will bring them together to watch, think, introspect and discuss on issues of relevance. 

Come together and have a good laugh!.........its as simple as that :-)
name: Stockholm International Film Club

description:
Kaleidoscope is a community for Virtual Reality Creators. Bringing together artists & engineers from cinema, gaming, and tech, Kaleidoscope explores virtual reality as a storytelling medium and celebrates the pioneers of this new art form. Creatives from all backgrounds are welcome!

We will host quarterly "Salons" where the community can showcase their virtual reality films, art, games, and immersive experiences. As a group, we will share knowledge, get feedback on projects, and show off our latest creations. 

We can't wait to meet you all! If you are interested in becoming a local organizer please email nick@kaleidovr.com. For more information about us, please visit kaleidovr.com.

category.name: movies/film
description:
Do you have a passion for film making or an interest in making movies? Whether you are a professional looking for collaborators, or a lover of films, you are welcome to join our group. The main aim of this group is to encourage creatives to implement their ideas in filmmaking and to bring ideas to life. 

There are many skilled and imaginative people out there, all they need is support and a network. One of the goals of this group is to work collectively most weekends and to complete one film a month. 

From time to time, we will organize workshops, seminars, outings, screenings, and the like, to further expand on our creative atmosphere and common love for film and filmmaking.

The concept of this group is simple, on weekends members of this group will meet and brainstorm ideas for producing a short format movie (under 15 minutes), then agree on a concept to produce for that month. We will bring projects from idea to script, through pre-production, production, and into final product by the end of the month. In other words, we will collaborate on shaping ideas, provide support during scriptwriting, shooting the short film, edit the footage, then publish the project online.

Please Note: This group is only for people who are passionate, respectful, and understanding. 
Just to confirm, this group will not generate any revenue in any case. We want to create and share our creations.
Everyone should contribute in some way or the other.
Since this is a non-profit group, time, equipment and resources needed for shooting films will be shared within the group members. We are here to help each other to create fun and exciting projects. Does this sound interesting? Step up, let's breathe new life into the ideas in our heads. If you have any questions please feel free to ask. Looking forward to see you. :)
name: Stockholm Filmmakers Collective
organizer.name: Ranjith Engu

category.name: movies/film
description:
Stockholm International Film Club is an ambitious Swedish Meetup initiative that endeavors to fuse quality contemporary cinema with commercial cinematic products from across the globe. The goal is to showcase, without any bias of origin or language, quality feature-films to the expats as well as the native audience residing in Sweden. This Meetup Group will exclusively acquire the rights to high quality international feature films for Sweden, and accordingly plan and schedule meetup events for anyone and everyone interested in quality cinema to come together, connect, network and share that common interest i.e. films!

Who should join?

Any film enthusiast, movie buff, film-goer; who is sincerely interested in experiencing the best of world cinema must join. With us, its not the Hollywood or Bollywood that matters, its not Europe or Asia that matters; what will make this film club meetup unique is the focus on content - the theme, the message, the cinematic experience - where cinema is an art which is honest, enjoyable, entertaining and at times, even hard-hitting.

What members can expect of the group, and what we expect of them.

We will introduce our members to the kind of cinema which has a message - on international issues, on social issues, on geopolitical issues - that can bring communities together, make them discuss on issues of relevance - presented in a format which is both enjoyable and entertaining. We wish that our members will come together to experience cinema as medium that will bring them together to watch, think, introspect and discuss on issues of relevance. 

Come together and have a good laugh!.........its as simple as that :-)
name: Stockholm International Film Club

Kaleidoscope is a community for Virtual Reality Creators. Bringing together artists & engineers from cinema, gaming, and tech, Kaleidoscope explores virtual reality as a storytelling medium and celebrates the pioneers of this new art form. Creatives from all backgrounds are welcome!

We will host quarterly "Salons" where the community can showcase their virtual reality films, art, games, and immersive experiences. As a group, we will share knowledge, get feedback on projects, and show off our latest creations. 

We can't wait to meet you all! If you are interested in becoming a local organizer please email nick@kaleidovr.com. For more information about us, please visit kaleidovr.com.

Copenhagen Cinema Club is for those who would like to enjoy films (and maybe coffe, drinks or food afterwards) with other people. You will normally find a wide range of independent, foreign and Danish films on this Meetup group, while Hollywood blockbusters will also pop up occasionally. 

The usual format is that we meet 30 min before the film and have a chat with each other in the cinema. After a movie, those, who have time, can join the group to a nearby cafe for a chat. 

Do you want to watch a specific movie? You are very welcome to post your suggestion on the meetup page or send a message to organizers. If you want, you can also become an organizer and post an event any time you want.

description:
Hi and thanks a lot for joining Copenhagen Blowjob Academy!

Please take a hard look at the calendar for an overview of meetups. Or use the 'Upcoming'/'Suggested' sections.

Our Concept:

We typically meet at an inexpensive to midrange restaurant for dinner, then head to the movies, sometimes followed by a post-movie group debriefing. During weekends, we sometimes meet for brunch and watch a movie afterwards.

What kind of movies do we like? Traditionally, we have watched a wide variety of movies, ranging from sci-fi and 3D movies to artsy movies. Hopefully you will find something you will like, or you can suggest a movie and be appointed event organizer. <br>

We expect participants at our social events to be well-mannered and -groomed. When someone does not know the Danish language, we will speak English. Check out the language of the next movie in the calendar. Most often, we will choose films with English-speaking characters, but occasionally, we may watch a movie that requires that you can read Danish subtitles.

Always bring cash to pay for the movie ticket at the event – or alternatively, bring a smart phone with the app Mobile Pay.

category.name: movies/film
description: The world of films is indeed exciting. For most of us who have a passion, it does seem impossible to be part of a movie production to learn more about the craft. This group is intended for amateurs (experts are also welcome) who are interested in different aspects of film making, screenplay, photography, acting etc. This is also the forum to work and experiment on projects like short films, documentaries to gain more knowledge on film making. You don't need to be an expert. All you need is passion for films and it's craft and also the mind to share and learn from each other.
name: Copenhagen Amateur Film Makers Meetup
organizer.name: Madhu John K

category.name: movies/film
description:
I love movies, especially at the cinema. But, it's often better if you can discuss the film over a couple of drinks afterwards.

This group is for anyone who wants to meet up in Malmö or Lund and go watch a film. There is no fixed agenda as yet (I'm making this up as I go along) and no specific type of film. Open to any suggestions - from the latest blockbusters to the classics.

Should also be a great way to meet new people and improve min dåliga svenska!
name: Malmö Lund Cinema Club
organizer.name: Craig Trim

category.name: movies/film
description:
We are now a great group who are making an independent project, We are in the process of developing developing a short film, and need people to join to make it happen. We would like anyone who is creative, has an interest for film and filmmaking, production, editing, actors from DP to Makeup artist.

We are a varied group in levels of experience, from amateur to those with more experience. We want to have fun and have a shared learning experience and challenge ourselves.

Our idea is basically a zombie apocalypse, more information and script is on our Facebook group.
Facebook group: Amateur filmmakers malmö

category.name: movies/film
description:
A place where fellow film makers can meet and collaborate to create films, and bring stories to life. 

Film making is a team effort and we believe collaboration is key

If you are involved with any of the following roles, we would be delighted to hear from you :)

Writer, Screenwriter, Cinematographer, Costume Designer, Art Director, Production Designer, Screenwriter, Director, Producer, Editor, Music Composer, Actor, Production Manager, Assistant Director, Stunt Coordinator, Location manager, Camera Operator, Sound Mixer, Boom Operator, Key Grip, Gaffer, Set Decorator, Make Up Artist, Colourist, Visual Effects Artist, Sound Editor, Casting Director, Storyboard Artist, Website Designer, Social Media, PR

Our goal is to meet, exchange and collaborate on making independent films and short films
name: Copenhagen Independent Filmmaking Meetup
organizer.name: Sunny Seth

category.name: movies/film
description:
This group is for future YouTubers, editors, journalists, camera people, directors, writers and anyone in between who want to create short, easy videos. This group is made to bring us all together and create a place where small projects can begin. So let's bring our passion together and make something great :D

This group is not meant as an advertising platform for jobs in the industry and you need to assume that all jobs that are advertised are voluntary.

We are currently moving over the Facebook. You can see our events in here but most of the activity is happening on Facebook. Come and join us!
https://www.facebook.com/groups/cphsvp

category.name: movies/film
description:
Shoot! is an international film festival with football documentaries
Football is passion, community, fanculture, idols, ups and downs. Football can gather a team, a local community, a city, even a nation. Football creates commun stories about us and our identity. Football is power, Football can change our lives and our society
Thats where SHOOT! starts.
Join the Shoot festival if you want to have a football experience outside the field
See you in the cinema
name: Shoot! Football Film Festival - Footbal Movies Meetup
